original: Didner, Gustaf Emanuel, bankdirektör, Jönköping, f. 11/2/91 i Alunda, Upps. 1. G. 24 m. Elisabet Jansson. Barn: Bengt f. 29, stud. — Stud:ex. i Upps. 11, Anst. v. Uppl. Ensk. Bank i Upps. 11, kamrer där 18-33, byråinsp. i bank- o. fbndinsp. 33-36, förste dito 36-43, verkst. dir. i A-B Smål. Bank sed. 43. Hobby: cykelfärder. RNO.
translated: Didner, Gustaf Emanuel, bank director, Jönköping, born 2/11/1891 in Alunda, Uppland, Sweden. He married Elisabet Jansson in 1924 and they had one child, Bengt, born in 1929 who studied and later became a clerk at Upplands Enskilda Bank in Uppsala in 1911. Gustaf himself also worked at the same bank, starting as a clerk in 1911, becoming head of department in 1933, and then managing director of A-B Smål. Bank in 1943. He had a hobby of cycling and was awarded RNO (Royal Order of the North Star).
